Package: codeometer
Version: 1.2.0
Section: base
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: bash (>= 4.0), findutils, coreutils, gawk
Maintainer: Best Codes <bestcodes.official@gmail.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/the-best-codes/codeometer
License: MIT
Description: A powerful command-line tool for analyzing code statistics across projects.
 This tool provides detailed code analysis for your projects, helping you understand
 your codebase size, composition, and structure. Features include:
  * Automatic project type detection (Node.js, Python, Java, Rust, Go, Ruby, PHP, C/C++)
  * Counts lines of code across multiple file types
  * Distinguishes between hand-written and auto-generated code
  * Optional comment line counting
  * Support for hidden files and directories
  * Colored and formatted output
  * Progress bar for large projects
Essential: no
Origin: Best Codes
